revision.text:
{{Location map-line|lat=71}}
{{kml}}
The '''71st parallel north''' is a [[circle of latitude]] that is 71 [[degree (angle)|degrees]] [[true north|north]] of the [[Earth|Earth's]] [[equator|equatorial plane]], in the [[Arctic]]. It crosses the [[Atlantic Ocean]], [[Europe]], [[Asia]] and [[North America]], and passes through some of the southern seas of the [[Arctic Ocean]].

At this latitude the [[sun]] is visible for 24 hours, 0 minutes during the [[summer solstice]] and Civil Twilight during the [[winter solstice]].

==Around the world==
Starting at the [[Prime Meridian]] and heading eastwards, the parallel 71° north passes through:

