{{For|the Roman Catholic bishop|Bishop of Portsmouth (Catholic)}} {{Infobox Bishopric |border = anglican |font_color = black |bishopric = [[Portsmouth]] |coatofarms = |image = |incumbent = [[Christopher Foster (bishop)|Christopher Foster]] |province = [[Province of Canterbury|Canterbury]] |diocese = [[Anglican Diocese of Portsmouth|Portsmouth]] |cathedral = [[Portsmouth Cathedral]] |residence=Bishopsgrove, [[Fareham]] |date = 1927 |website = }} The '''Bishop of Portsmouth''' is the [[Ordinary (officer)|Ordinary]] of the [[Church of England]] [[Anglican Diocese of Portsmouth|Diocese of Portsmouth]] in the [[Province of Canterbury]].
The diocese covers south-east [[Hampshire]] and the [[Isle of Wight]] and has its [[Episcopal see|see]] in the [[Portsmouth|City of Portsmouth]], where the [[Cathedra|seat]] is located at the [[Portsmouth Cathedral|Cathedral Church of Saint Thomas of Canterbury]] which was elevated to cathedral status in 1927. The bishop's residence is Bishopsgrove, [[Fareham]].
The office of bishop was created in 1927 when the new diocese was formed from part of the [[Diocese of Winchester]]. The current bishop is the Right Reverend [[Christopher Foster (bishop)|Christopher Foster]], the 9th Bishop of Portsmouth, who signs ''+ Christopher Portsmouth''. Previously [[Bishop of Hertford|Suffragan Bishop of Hertford]], his nomination as Bishop of Portsmouth was announced by [[10 Downing Street|Downing Street]] on 9 February 2010.<ref name=bpforsternominated>{{cite news|url=http://www.hampshirechronicle.co.uk/news/4995955.New_bishop_for_south_east_Hampshire/|title=New bishop for south-east Hampshire|date=9 February 2010|work=Hampshire Chronicle|accessdate=9 February 2010|location=Winchester, Hampshire}}</ref> He was installed and enthroned in a service at [[Portsmouth Cathedral]] on 18 September 2010.<ref name=bpforsterinstalled>[https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-england-hampshire-11353057 Service to install Bishop of Portsmouth]. ''BBC''. Published on 18 September 2010.</ref>
