{{Unreferenced|date=October 2010}} {{Infobox road |country=DOM |marker_image=none |type=DR |route=12 |alternate_name=Carretera de Constanza |maint= |map= |length_mi= |length_round= |length_ref= |established= |direction_a=East |terminus_a= [[DR-1]], near [[Bonao]], [[Dominican Republic|DR]] |beltway_city= |junction= |direction_b=West |terminus_b=[[Constanza, Dominican Republic|Constanza]], [[Dominican Republic|DR]] |towns= Angostura, Tireo, Constanza |previous_type= |previous_route= |next_type= |next_route= }}
'''DR-12''', better known as la '''Carretera de Constanza''', is a signed highway in the [[Dominican Republic]], part of the national highway system. DR-12 connects the main highway of the Republic, [[DR-1]], with the middle sized town of [[Constanza, Dominican Republic|Constanza]]. Recently renovated, DR-12 is the only connection to the fertile valley of Constanza which is high in the [[Cordillera Central, Dominican Republic|Cordillera Central]]. It was recently renovated in 2010. It is widely known for the natural beauty that surrounds it and also for the dangers of driving in it.
