A '''shutter ridge''' is a [[ridge]] which has moved along a [[Geologic fault|fault]] line, blocking or diverting drainage. Typically, a shutter ridge creates a valley corresponding to the alignment of the fault that produces it.<ref>[https://earthquake.usgs.gov/hazards/qfaults/glossary.php#S Glossary, Earthquake Hazards Program, USGS] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140929074256/http://earthquake.usgs.gov/hazards/qfaults/glossary.php |date=2014-09-29 }}</ref> Shutter ridges occur exclusively at [[strike-slip fault]]s.
